test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7d3b7e7dff40>([-7])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7d3b7e7dff40> = [[1, -7], [1, -7, 1], [-7], [-7, 1], [1, -7], [1, -7, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7d3b7e7dff40>([1, -7])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7d3b7e7dff40> = [[1, -7], [1, -7, 1], [-7], [-7, 1], [1, -7], [1, -7, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x7d3b7e7dff40>([-7, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x7d3b7e7dff40> = [[1, -7], [1, -7, 1], [-7], [-7, 1], [1, -7], [1, -7, 1], ...].count
test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 1 == -7
 +  where 1 = <built-in function prod>([])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
